Artur Mkrtichyan, the first leader of Artsakh, and indeed much of the original leadership--including Georgi Petrosian, Mkrtichyan's successor--were all ARF members. The leadership situation really only changes with Levon Ter-Petrosyan imposing his will on the conflict and introducing Kocharyan/Sargsyan.
